# UI simplicity (Medora-S)

The interface must be usable by **clinicians with minimal training**.

## Prefer

- **Simple forms** — few fields per step, obvious labels (French per product language rule)
- **Clear tables** — readable columns, obvious actions
- **Minimal modals** — use only when necessary; prefer inline or dedicated pages when flow is heavy
- **Few navigation layers** — shallow menus; user reaches task in few clicks

## Avoid

- **Complex dashboard widgets** (heavy charts, dense “command center” layouts) unless clearly MVP-needed
- **Excessive filtering** — many simultaneous filters, advanced query builders
- **Deep nested navigation** — menus within menus, long drill-downs

## When adding UI

- Ask: *Can someone learn this in one short walkthrough?*
- Default to **boring and clear** over clever and dense.
